'''ReText''' is a simple but powerful text editor for '''Markdown''' and '''reStructuredText''' with '''"Live preview"''' function

== Installation ==

[[File:Retext_main_window.png|300px|thumb|right|retext 2-panel view]]

ReText is not availible in main portage tree, so it is contained in a [http://gpo.zugaina.org/Overlays/gentoo-zh gentoo-zh] Overlay - [http://gpo.zugaina.org/app-text/retext retext] package

{{Note| For more information regarding overlays, please read the [[overlay]] article.}}

Adding overlay:

{{RootCmd| layman --add gentoo-zh}}

Than emerge as standart program:

{{Emerge|retext}}

=== Troubles ===

If you starting ReText and getting message as this:

{{Code|retext output|<pre>Traceback (most recent call last):
File "/usr/bin/retext", line 1530, in <module>
  main(sys.argv[1:])
File "/usr/bin/retext", line 1517, in main
  window = ReTextWindow()
File "/usr/bin/retext", line 547, in __init__
  self.tabWidget.addTab(self.createTab(""), self.tr('New document'))
File "/usr/bin/retext", line 605, in createTab
  if self.useWebKit:
AttributeError: 'ReTextWindow' object has no attribute 'useWebKit'</pre>}}


you need build  {{Package|dev-python/PyQt4}} with '''webkit USE flag'''. [http://www.gentoo.org/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=2&chap=2 Official USE Flag Documentation]

{{Note|
If you switch on ''webkit USE flag'' for {{Package|PyQt4}}, it require install {{Package|libxml2}} with ''icu USE flag''. If this generate unsolvable portage conflicts, try make '''icu as global USE flag''' and re-emerge world.}}

